data.Name: Apparent
data.Description: The phase velocity that a wavefront appears to have along a line of geophones.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Average
data.Description: The distance traversed divided by the time required, both with respect to some particular travel path and with respect to a datum.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Instantaneous
data.Description: The speed at any given moment of a wavefront in the direction of the energy propagation.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Interval
data.Description: The average velocity over some interval of travel path.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Normal moveout
data.Description: The velocity for the normal-moveout correction in the limit as the source-receiver distance becomes very small.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Root mean square
data.Description: The square root of the average of the squares of a series of measurements. The autocorrelation value (without normalising) for zero lag is the mean square value.
data.AttributionPublication: Encyclopedic Dictionary Of Applied Geophysics, Third Edition
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Dix
data.Description: Indicates that the Velocity has been computed using Dix formula
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Migration
data.Description: Indicates that the Velocity type is a Migration velocity
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: NMO
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="NormalMoveout" with Name="Normal moveout" instead. Indicates that the Velocity type is a Normal Moveout velocity
